crontab -e

-----------

Select editor (1-3). Then edit file to introduce task to be run in this format:
* * * * * your_task.sh

Each star has time setting.
First  - minute (0-59)
Second - hour (0-23) * means every hour
Third  - day of the month, 1-31: * means every day of the month
Fourth - month, 1-12: * means every month
Fifth  - day of the week, 0-7 (0 and 7 are both Sunday): * means every day

Save and close file. Task is install.

To check your tasks write command:

crontab -l
